About
MYPO was formed by youth from different areas of Mon and Karen states in 2001, with the aim of supporting the struggle for democracy, human rights and building a strong civil society for peaceful and democratic change in Burma.

General Information
Mon Youth Progressive Organization (MYPO) is an independent youth organization comprised of Mon youth from different townships in Mon State, Karen State and Thanintary Division. Every two year, MYPO conducts its conference and elects members of the leading committee by secret vote.
1999, June 18, a group of Mon youth came together and shared an idea of forming a represent youth organization to work for Mon youth, for the community, for Nation and to train youth to become leader among Mon communities. In 2001, November 18, MYPO was systematically founded in Thai-Burma border, Sangkhalaburi, Thailand. 
MYPO works on the empowerment of young men and women, the promotion of democratic practices and equal rights, the sound development of civil society sector, and the preservation of Mon literature and culture. 
MYPO allies with Students and Youth Congress of Burma (SYCB), Mon Youth Forum (MYF), Burma River Network (BRN), Rehmonnya Peace Foundation (RPF) and Save the Salween Network (SSN). Moreover, MYPO’s partners are Mon CSO, Township Based Mon Youth Organizations in Mon State and Karen State and New Mon State Party. Civic Society Organization. 
The Target Areas of MYPO are Poung, Malamyine, Choung Zone, Kyite Mayaw, Mudon, Thanphyzayat, Ye Township in Mon State, Kyar Inn Seik Kyi, Hpa’an and Kaw Krait Township in Karen State and Ye Phyu Township in Thanintary Division. 
